            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "Funding $9 billion for NASA Science sustains U.S. space leadership and local innovation. In RI-2, NASA has invested $2.9M since FY23, supporting critical work at the University of Rhode Island on astronomical detectors and PACE ocean science, as well as Europa modeling at Providence College. This funding ensures the U.S. remains competitive against rising international space ambitions while supporting a high-tech local workforce.",
